    <Directions>
        <Steps>
            
            <StepDescription StepNumber = "1">
                Preheat the oven to 350째F (175째C), and butter a 4x8-inch loaf pan.
            </StepDescription>
            
            <StepDescription StepNumber = "2">
                In a mixing bowl, mash the ripe bananas with a fork until smooth. Stir the melted butter into the mashed bananas.
            </StepDescription>
            
            <StepDescription StepNumber = "3">
                Mix in the baking soda and salt. Stir in the sugar, beaten egg, and vanilla extract. Mix in the flour.
            </StepDescription>
            
            <StepDescription StepNumber = "4">
                Pour the batter into your prepared loaf pan. Bake for 1 hour to 1 hour 10 minutes (check at 50 minutes) at 350째F (175째C), or until a tester inserted into the center comes out clean.
            </StepDescription>
            
            <StepDescription StepNumber = "5">
                While oil is heating up to 360F. Combine flour with spices, salt and pepper.
            </StepDescription>
            
            <StepDescription StepNumber = "6">
                Remove from oven and cool completely on a rack. Remove the banana bread from the pan. Slice and serve. (A bread knife helps to make slices that aren't crumbly.)
            </StepDescription>
        </Steps>
    </Directions>

